---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Quick Start | CodeFi Docs">
  <div slot="header">
    <div class="text-neon-green font-mono text-sm mb-2">/ GETTING STARTED</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Quick Start</h1>
  </div>

  <p>Once installed, CodeFi is designed to get you into flow in under 10 seconds.</p>

  <h2>1. Initialize</h2>
  <p>Run the initialization command to set up your local database and config files.</p>
  <pre><code>codefi init</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Play Music</h2>
  <p>Start with the default curated library. No accounts needed for basic tracks.</p>
  <pre><code>codefi play</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Control Playback</h2>
  <p>Use the global hotkeys or the command interface to manage your session.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>codefi stop</code>: Stop music immediately.</li>
    <li><code>codefi status</code>: See what's playing.</li>
    <li><code>codefi volume --up</code>: Raise the intensity.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-cyber-darker border border-cyber-gray rounded-xl">
    <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-4">Pro Tip: Aliases</h3>
    <p class="text-cyber-text text-sm">
      Most users alias <code>codefi</code> to <code>cf</code> in their <code>.zshrc</code> or <code>.bashrc</code>:
    </p>
    <pre><code>alias cf='codefi'</code></pre>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
